# JavaScript

## Architecture

```
src/js/
├── main.js          # Entry point — imports libs + initializes features via ready()
├── components/      # 1 file = 1 component, named export (15+ components: accordion,
│                    # header, search, carousels, cms, datepicker, lazyload-video,
│                    # marquee, select, tooltip, video-placeholder, input-file,
│                    # backtop, accessibility, footer)
├── pages/           # Page-specific logic (e.g. home.js gated by body class)
└── utils/           # ready(), lity, jquery-touch-reset, …
```

Bundled via **Webpack 5** (see `src/tasks/webpack.js`): entry `js/main.js` → `dist/js/main.min.js` (Terser-minified). `ProvidePlugin` wires `Popper` and `bootstrap` globally — verify any extra alias actually matches an installed package.

## Libraries available (import on demand)

| Library | Role | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Bootstrap 5** JS | dropdowns, accordions, modals, offcanvas | `import 'bootstrap'` — no jQuery required |
| **AOS** | scroll animations | `import AOS from 'aos'; AOS.init({…})` — pair with `data-aos="…"` |
| **Lity** | lightbox (video/image) | local util in `utils/lity.js` — mark triggers with `data-lity` |
| **Splide** (+ auto-scroll, video) | carousels / marquees | `import Splide from '@splidejs/splide'` |
| **Swiper** | advanced carousels (a11y pagination, tabs) | `import Swiper from 'swiper/bundle'` |
| **Rellax** | parallax effects | light, JS-only |
| **Choices.js** | enhanced `<select>` | with a11y wiring |
| **Flatpickr** | date pickers | pair with `components/forms/_flatpickr.scss` |
| **Select2** | legacy select enhancement | prefer Choices.js in new projects |
| **intl-tel-input** | international phone inputs | flag images copied to `dist/vendor/` via `copy-vendor` |
| **tarteaucitronjs** | cookie consent (CNIL) | loaded from `dist/vendor/` (NOT bundled) — see cookie template |
| **GSAP** | complex animations | use only when Bootstrap/AOS are not enough |

## Component pattern

```js
// ❌ BAD — scattered DOMContentLoaded, anonymous functions
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  document.querySelectorAll('.accordion').forEach(...);
});

// ✅ GOOD — named export, centralized init in main.js, early return guard
export const accordion = () => {
  const items = document.querySelectorAll('.js-accordion');
  if (!items.length) return;
  items.forEach((item) => { /* ... */ });
};
```

Then in `main.js`:

```js
import 'bootstrap';
import AOS from 'aos';
import { ready } from './utils/utils';
import { accordion } from './components/accordion';
import { header } from './components/header';

ready(() => {
  AOS.init({ once: true, duration: 600 });
  accordion();
  header();
});
```

## Rules

1. **Early return** if the DOM target does not exist (`if (!el) return;`)
2. Target the DOM via **`js-*` classes** (never styling classes)
3. State classes on targets: **`is-*`** (`.is-active`, `.is-open`, `.is-loading`) — note: some legacy projects use bare `active` / `clicked` / `overflow` on `<html>`/`<body>`, follow project's local convention.
4. Configuration via **`data-*`** attributes, never hardcoded constants (Bootstrap uses `data-bs-*` prefix)
5. Do not import jQuery unless strictly required by a vendor script (Bootstrap 5 no longer needs it)
6. Use **`ready()`** from `utils/utils.js` rather than raw `DOMContentLoaded`
7. Page-specific scripts should self-gate: `if (!document.body.classList.contains('home')) return;`

## Accessibility in JS

- Mobile menu: manage focus trap + `aria-expanded` on trigger + `Escape` to close
- Modals / dropdowns: restore focus to the trigger on close
- Never `removeAttribute('tabindex')` on a natively focusable element
- Splide/Swiper: add `aria-roledescription="carousel"` on the root, `aria-label` on prev/next buttons (use `visually-hidden` text for screen-reader-only labels)
